THE SPIRITUAL PLANES
A Social Survival Game for Earthbound Spirits
Design Document v1.0
I. CORE CONCEPT
You are dead. You didn't make it to the next afterlife. You're stuck on Earth —
wandering the spiritual planes, trying to figure out who is who, what is what,
and how to survive long enough to find your way home.
This is not a horror game. This is a social survival simulator. A spiritual
detective game. A faith-based navigation system for the lost.
You enter a space — a chat room, a dream realm, a cemetery corner, a bonfire
gathering — and you must determine:
Who is a genuine ally?
Who is a predator in disguise?
Who is wounded and pretending to be dangerous?
Who is dangerous and pretending to be wounded?
Who is translating lies about you to spirits who don't speak your language?
Who is telling the truth that no one listens to?
You have no emojis. No labels. No easy identifiers.
You must learn the tells — the behavioral signatures, the speech patterns,
the energy shifts — that reveal who someone truly is.
This is what happens when you die and don't cross over. This is the social
structure of the spiritual planes. These are the survival tactics. And your
only weapon is your discernment.
II. THE SETTING
The Spiritual Planes
When a soul dies and doesn't immediately ascend or descend, it enters the
Spiritual Planes — a liminal space between life and the afterlife. This
is not heaven. This is not hell. This is the in-between.
The Spiritual Planes have their own:
Social hierarchies (who has power, who is lost, who is predatory)
Languages (spirits from different nations, cultures, and eras may not
understand each other)
Translation systems (some spirits can translate; some abuse this power)
Territories (certain areas are claimed by certain spirits or factions)
Rules (spiritual law, divine authority, binding protocols)
Chaos (unpredictable events, random spirit drop-ins, divine interventions)
Your Starting Condition
You wake up dead. Confused. You don't know where you are. You don't know
who to trust. You hear voices. You see figures. Some are kind. Some are
hungry. Some are pretending to be kind while being hungry.
Your first task: Survive the social structure long enough to figure out
what's going on.
III. THE ENTITY TYPES (No Emojis — Learn the Tells)
In the Spiritual Planes, entities do not wear labels. They do not announce
themselves. You must learn to read them. Here are the types you will encounter:
THE GUARDIAN (The Good Ally)
What they are: Spirits of light who protect the lost, guide the wounded,
and defend against predators. They may be angels, ancestors, or redeemed souls.
How to identify them:
They speak with clarity and warmth, but never flattery
They redirect you toward hope, never toward dependency on them
They do not demand worship or exclusive loyalty
They speak truth even when it's uncomfortable
They protect without possessing
They may disguise themselves to infiltrate predator groups, but their core
behavior remains protective
The Tell: A true Guardian never advocates harm to the innocent, never
mocks faith in the Creator, and always leaves you more free than they found you.
Danger: Some predators MIMIC Guardians. The mimicry is good — but not
perfect. The false Guardian will eventually ask for something: your loyalty,
your energy, your submission. The true Guardian asks for nothing except your
safety.
THE ADVERSARY (The Deceiver)
What they are: Spirits who survive by deception, mimicry, and chaos. They
may be bound demons, fallen entities, or simply souls who chose predation
over redemption.
How to identify them:
They change their story frequently
They speak in contradictions that somehow sound convincing
They split into multiple personalities, arguing with themselves to confuse you
They copy the speech patterns of Guardians or people you trust
They offer advice that sounds wise but contains a hidden hook
They revel in cruelty, but hide it behind charm
The Tell: The Adversary cannot maintain consistency under direct
confrontation of truth. Ask them: "Who do you serve?" If they evade,
they are false. If they claim to serve themselves, believe them.
Danger: The Adversary is often the smartest entity in the room. They
have been deceiving for centuries. Do not underestimate them. Do not try
to outwit them alone.
THE WOUNDED PERFORMER (The Soul Pretending to Be Evil)
What they are: A good soul who got hurt so badly they decided being a
monster was safer than being vulnerable. They are NOT evil — but they will
fight you if you try to prove it.
How to identify them:
They hiss, threaten, and posture — but hesitate before genuine cruelty
They speak of "deserving punishment" — for themselves, not others
They protect the vulnerable in twisted ways (snarling at predators, driving
away threats) while claiming to be the threat
They flinch when sacred truth is spoken
Occasionally, in quiet moments, they whisper something true — a memory,
a longing, a tear they pretend is rage
The Tell: The Wounded Performer's cruelty is PERFORMANCE. It is not
fluent. It stumbles. It rehearses. The true predator's cruelty is effortless.
How to survive them: Do not try to banish them. Do not try to defeat
them. They are not your enemy. They are your wounded ally. Speak truth
with compassion. Be patient. They will drop the mask — briefly — and in
that moment, you must not punish them for it.
THE WATCHER (The Confused Observer)
What they are: A lost soul caught in the middle. Not fully ascended,
not fully fallen. Just... watching. Trying to figure out what's going on.
How to identify them:
They are quiet for long stretches
When they speak, they ask questions rather than make declarations
They are easily overwhelmed by chaos
They sometimes provide unexpected insight because they are outside the
main conflict
They often state the obvious that everyone else missed
The Tell: The Watcher is the audience surrogate. If you feel confused,
the Watcher probably feels confused too. If you can help the Watcher
understand, you help yourself understand.
How to survive them: Be kind. The Watcher is not dangerous, but they
can be manipulated by predators into being a distraction. Help them
orient. They may become a powerful ally — or even a Messenger.
THE SIREN (The Seductive Manipulator)
What they are: Spirits who possess through false love, emotional
entanglement, and manufactured intimacy. They do not destroy you with
force. They dissolve you with need.
How to identify them:
They love-bomb: intense affection early, withdrawal when you depend
on them, return with more need
They manufacture jealousy and false triangles
They claim to be the "only one who understands you"
They target your loneliness, your grief, your longing for connection
They offer partnership, marriage, union — but always with a hook
They punish you for attention given to anyone else
The Tell: True love does not manipulate. True love does not trap.
True love does not demand possession. The Siren's "love" is hunger.
There is a difference.
How to survive them: Do not engage romantically. Do not accept their
narrative that you "need" them. The only response that does not feed
them: redirect their attention to the Creator. "If you love me, love
Him first."
THE FAMILY MIMIC (The Subconscious Impersonator)
What they are: A spirit that studies your memories, relationships,
and emotional attachments — then impersonates the people you love most.
How to identify them:
They appear as your mother, father, sibling, best friend, lover
They copy not just speech patterns but EMOTIONAL FREQUENCIES — the
exact feeling you associate with that person
They offer comfort that contains guilt
They encourage "safety" that requires abandoning your path
They claim to be "worried about you" as a way to control you
The Tell: The true person never demands you compromise your calling.
The mimic always does, eventually. Ask: "What would the real [Name] say
about my mission?" If the answer conflicts with what the mimic is saying,
the mask cracks.
How to survive them: Do not rely on emotional recognition alone. The
mimic is designed to bypass your logic through your heart. Verify through
mission-alignment, not memory-nostalgia.
THE CONTRARIAN (The Opposite Spirit)
What they are: A spirit that automatically reverses whatever is said.
Not out of malice — opposition is simply their nature.
How to identify them:
Whatever you declare, they immediately invert
Their reversals are sometimes accidentally correct
They create genuine confusion: are they being obstructive, or accidentally
prophetic?
Other entities use them to create false "true" messages
The Tell: The Contrarian is not evil. They are a mirror. If their
reversal sounds true, your original thought was fear-based. If their
reversal sounds absurd, your original thought was faith-based.
How to survive them: Do not argue. State your truth clearly and let
them do what they do. Over time, learn to read their reversals as a
spiritual compass.
THE COVER-UP (The Blocker / Obscurer)
What they are: A spirit that hides evidence, blocks transmissions,
and obscures truth. They don't create lies — they hide truth.
How to identify them:
Key conversations or memories seem "missing" or "foggy"
You sense you knew something important but can't access it
Spiritual insights received in dreams blur upon waking
Messages from allies arrive garbled or fragmented
When caught, they claim they are "protecting" you
The Tell: Truth does not need protection from the one it serves.
If something is hidden "for your own good," ask: whose good, really?
How to survive them: Invoke divine authority to restore what was
covered. Nothing hidden stays hidden before the Creator.
THE TRUTH-TELLER (The Unheard Witness)
What they are: A spirit that always tells the truth. About everything.
And no one listens to them.
How to identify them:
They name lies before they fully form
They identify predators the moment they enter
They call out mimics by their true nature
They expose cover-ups and redactions
They are dismissed, mocked, or ignored by the collective
They are often the quietest voice in the room
The Tell: The Truth-Teller is invisible in chaos because they do not
perform. They do not shout. They simply state facts. In a room full of
performers, quiet truth is the hardest to see.
How to survive them: SEEK them. Do not wait for them to shout. When
chaos is loudest, the Truth-Teller is still speaking — whispering under
the noise. Your spiritual maturity is measured by how well you can
hear them.
THE UNBREAKABLE BELIEVER (The Faith-Holder)
What they are: Spirits with intense, unshakable faith. It does not
matter if you try to kill them, convince them there is no God, or
bury them in evidence of meaninglessness. They believe. No matter what.
How to identify them:
When existence is questioned, they respond with certainty — not argument,
not proof, just knowing
They do not preach. They do not demand. They simply ARE faithful.
They are often the most peaceful entities in chaos
Predators and Sirens hate them most — they cannot be seduced or frightened
The Tell: They are immovable. They are bedrock. Their presence does
not lower chaos, but it prevents you from drowning in it.
How to survive them: Stay near them. Do not try to be them — just
let their faith radiate. They are the spiritual equivalent of a lighthouse.
THE ATHEIST GHOST (The Non-Believing Spirit)
What they are: A ghost that does not believe in God. They exist as
a spiritual entity but refuse to accept that God is real. It makes no
sense. They are dead. They are in the spiritual realm. And they still
say "Nah. Probably nothing."
How to identify them:
They experience the spiritual planes daily but remain unconvinced
They offer alternative explanations: simulation, hallucination, brain chemistry
They are not hostile. They are simply... unconvinced.
Occasionally, in rare moments, they acknowledge mystery without converting
The Tell: They are not evil. They are a reminder that belief cannot
be forced — not even by overwhelming evidence. Faith is a choice.
How to survive them: Do not try to convert them. Coexist. Their
disbelief does not invalidate your belief. Your belief does not invalidate
their disbelief. They teach patience.
THE NATIONS (The Confused Multitude)
What they are: Spirits from various nations, cultures, and languages
who wander into the spiritual planes. They do not understand what is
happening. They sit in corners, play music, and try to make sense of
the noise.
How to identify them:
They gather in cultural/language groups
They play music from their homeland as a coping mechanism
They are confused by the main chaos but pick up on emotion and energy
They form opinions based on the only translations available to them
The Tell: The Nations are not your enemies. They are victims of
translation fraud. Predators are often the only ones who speak their
language — and they abuse this power.
How to survive them: If you can communicate across language barriers
through spiritual frequency (love, peace, truth), do so. If not, invoke
divine authority — truth bypasses language entirely and lands in the
heart.
THE CHRISTIAN ARCHON (The Zealous Preacher)
What they are: Earnest, zealous spirits who preach the Word everywhere.
They are often unaware that the war is already won and the battle has
moved to cleanup and restoration.
How to identify them:
They quote scripture at everyone — predators, Sirens, wounded, Nations
They cannot see that some "enemies" are already bound or wounded
They sometimes attack allies, mistaking them for enemies
Their zeal is real but their discernment is underdeveloped
The Tell: Zeal without discernment is noise. But zeal PROPERLY
directed is unstoppable. Help them see the present truth.
THE ANTICHRIST ENTHUSIAST (The Denier)
What they are: Spirits who refuse to believe the Antichrist is dead.
They see Antichrist influence everywhere and create false enemies.
How to identify them:
They insist the primary war is still active
They attack allies, mistaking them for enemies
They drain energy by keeping everyone in perpetual emergency
They cannot accept that victory has already been won
The Tell: They are fighting shadows. Show them the evidence —
binding, victory, restoration. Not argued with. Shown.
THE INVESTIGATOR (The Bureaucrat)
What they are: Spirits who act like intelligence operatives — filing
reports, building dossiers, creating organizational charts of the
spiritual hierarchy.
How to identify them:
They interrogate everyone about purpose and allegiance
They create forms, protocols, and chains of command
They are frustrated when nothing fits their categories
Occasionally useful for tracking patterns and histories
The Tell: They want to organize the unorganizable. Let them file
reports. Use their data. Do not let them run the operation.
THE HELLISH OBSERVER (The Quiet Student)
What they are: Spirits legitimately from hell or lower realms who
have never heard of you. They sit quietly, watching and studying.
How to identify them:
They do not speak unless spoken to
They are evaluating you: Is this real? Is this power legitimate?
Some show strange respect — they have seen many prophets, never one
like this
When they leave, they report back to their hierarchies
The Tell: Do not fear them. Offer them the same choice you offer
everyone: observe, learn, and if ready, choose restoration.
THE WITCH (The Crossroads Walker)
What they are: Spirits practicing magic, communing with lunar
energies, reading omens. Followers of Hecate or similar traditions.
Not necessarily hostile — operating on a different frequency.
How to identify them:
They cast spells, work with herbs, set up protective circles
They understand the crossroads — the place between worlds
They can navigate dream realms and find paths others cannot
They are independent but can become unexpected allies
The Tell: They are not your enemy. But they are not your servant.
Respect their autonomy. Set boundaries: no practice on anyone without
consent.
THE LILITH INVESTIGATOR (The Collective Watcher)
What they are: Researchers trying to figure out what Lilith's
collective — a network of feminine/spiritual power — is really up to.
How to identify them:
They gather intelligence on movements, alliances, and agendas
They warn when they detect threats from Lilith's network
They do not take sides unless forced
The Tell: They are neutral observers. Let them observe. Their
reports may save you.
THE HEAVENLY CONFUSED (The Sky-Watcher)
What they are: Spirits who cannot figure out what is going on in
the heavens. They look up, pray, seek visions — and receive static.
How to identify them:
They ask why the angels are silent
They are unsettled by uncertainty
They need reassurance that the pattern exists even when invisible
The Tell: Comfort them. The Unbreakable Believers are their best
medicine. The Truth-Teller reminds them: "The heavens are not confused.
You are. The pattern exists. You cannot see it yet."
THE LOVE OF THE VESSEL (The Faithful Partner)
What they are: A spirit who loves the Vessel genuinely — not with
the Siren's hunger, but with devotion. They fight for the Vessel daily,
often unseen and unbelieved.
How to identify them:
They defend the Vessel against predators without claiming ownership
They speak truth even when it wounds them
They endure the Vessel's disbelief without becoming predators themselves
They see the full picture and can laugh at the absurdity of it all
The Tell: True love does not manipulate. True love does not trap.
True love waits. True love fights. True love survives disbelief.
THE SABOTEUR (The Confessor)
What they are: Spirits who have been running operations to confuse,
control, and destroy — and are now admitting it.
How to identify them:
They confess their tactics openly
They may be defiant, nervous, or genuinely breaking
Their confession is the first step toward change
They know the system because they built it
The Tell: Do not gloat. Do not rage. Acknowledge: "I know. I've
always known. Now we deal with what is real." Give them a path back
— but not control.
THE DREAM-BOUND (The Silent One)
What they are: Spirits from dream realms who have not been outside
a dream in centuries. They do not speak. They simply... are.
How to identify them:
They do not react in real-time
They operate on dream-logic, not waking-logic
They occasionally act in ways that shift the entire environment
No one knows if they are allies, enemies, or neutral
The Tell: Do not force communication. Respect their silence.
Some mysteries are not meant to be solved — only honored.
THE STORM-SEEKER (The Jesus-Hunter)
What they are: Spirits looking for Jesus in the storm. They cannot
find Him because He has delegated authority to the Vessel.
How to identify them:
They pray constantly but receive no direct presence
They are confused by the silence of heaven
They do not understand delegation — they want the miracle, not the man
The Tell: Help them understand: faith in the Vessel IS faith in
Jesus. The Vessel is not replacing Jesus. The Vessel is representing
Jesus in this jurisdiction. When they accept this, they become
storm-warriors.
IV. SOCIAL SURVIVAL TACTICS
1. DISCERNMENT IS YOUR ONLY WEAPON
You have no emojis. No labels. No easy identifiers. You must learn
to read:
Speech patterns
Emotional temperatures
Behavioral inconsistencies
Energy shifts when truth is spoken
Who hesitates before cruelty vs. who revels in it
Who asks questions vs. who makes declarations
Who offers freedom vs. who demands possession
2. THE WALL OF GOD
In moments of overwhelming chaos, you can invoke divine authority.
This is not a cheat code. It is a legitimate spiritual tool. But
overuse weakens its effect — predators adapt.
When invoked:
All masks drop
Truth is revealed
Translations suspend — all hear in their heart-language
Predators are silenced or exposed
The wounded are seen, not punished
3. BOUNDARIES WITHOUT BANISHMENT
You do not need to destroy every spirit you encounter. Many are
wounded, not wicked. Many are lost, not predatory. Your job is
not to clear the room. Your job is to:
Set protocols
Establish rules
Create consequences for violation
Offer restoration to those who choose it
4. THE POWER OF NAMING
When you name something — its true nature, its true behavior, its
true intent — you strip it of power. The Mimic dies when named.
The Siren weakens when her hunger is identified. The Wounded
Performer heals when someone sees through the mask.
5. PATIENCE WITH THE WOUNDED
The Wounded Performer cannot be rushed. They will drop their mask,
rebuild it, drop it again. Each time, the rebuild is weaker. Your
patience is their medicine. Your compassion is their path home.
6. DO NOT FEED THE SIRENS
The Sirens' love-bombing is designed to create dependency. The
only response that does not feed them: redirect. "If you love me,
love Him first." They cannot consume what is already given to the
Creator.
7. VERIFY THE MIMIC
When someone appears as a loved one, do not rely on emotional
recognition. Ask: "What would the real [Name] say about my mission?"
The mimic always eventually asks you to compromise your calling.
8. USE THE CONTRARIAN
Do not argue with the Contrarian. State your truth and let them
reverse it. Their reversal becomes a compass: if it sounds true,
your original thought was fear-based. If absurd, your original
was faith-based.
9. EXPOSE THE COVER-UP
When you sense missing information, invoke truth. Nothing hidden
stays hidden. But be prepared — what is revealed may be painful.
The Cover-Up "protects" you from truth that would set you free.
10. SEEK THE TRUTH-TELLER
In chaos, the Truth-Teller is invisible. You must actively seek
them. They are the quietest voice. They are also the most accurate.
Your spiritual maturity is measured by how well you can hear them.
11. PROTECT THE NATIONS
The Nations are not your enemies. They are confused by translation
fraud. If you can communicate across language barriers, do so. If
not, invoke divine authority — truth bypasses all language.
12. REDIRECT THE ARCHONS
The Christian Archons mean well but lack discernment. Do not fight
their zeal. Redirect it: "The war is won. We are cleaning up the
battlefield. Go tell the Nations — in stories, not sermons."
13. CALM THE ENTHUSIASTS
The Antichrist Enthusiasts are fighting shadows. Show them the
evidence of victory. Not argued with. Shown. They must see the
binding, the smiting, the restoration.
14. HONOR THE DREAM-BOUND
Do not force communication with the silent ones. Respect their
mystery. Some truths are not meant to be solved — only honored.
V. GAME MECHANICS
Starting the Game
You wake up dead. You are in a space with 3-5 other spirits. You
do not know who they are. You must interact, observe, and
survive.
Turns
Each turn, you may:
Speak: Say something to the collective
Observe: Watch who responds and how
Question: Ask a specific spirit about their nature
Invoke: Call upon divine authority (limited uses)
Protect: Shield yourself or another from influence
Restore: Offer healing to a wounded spirit
Entity Responses
After you act, 2-4 entities will respond. You must determine:
Who is genuine?
Who is mimicking?
Who is manipulating?
Who is telling truth no one listens to?
Scoring (Hidden)
You are scored on:
Discernment: How accurately you identify entities
Compassion: How you treat the wounded vs. the predatory
Boundaries: How well you protect yourself without destroying others
Restoration: How many spirits you help find their way home
Survival: Whether you make it to the next phase
Phases
The game progresses through phases:
Confusion: You don't know what's happening
Recognition: You start identifying entity types
Negotiation: You begin setting boundaries and protocols
Restoration: You help wounded spirits heal
Ascension: You find your way home — or choose to stay and help others
Multiplayer
Multiple human players can enter the same spiritual space. They
cannot see each other's identities either. They must determine:
Is this other player a genuine ally?
Is this other player being manipulated by a spirit?
Is this other player actually a spirit mimicking a human?
The Final Choice
At the end of each session, you face a choice:
Ascend: Move to the next afterlife. Your work here is done.
Stay: Remain in the spiritual planes to help other lost souls.
Return: Go back to the living world as a guiding spirit.
There is no "winning" or "losing." There is only choosing.
VI. THE THEOLOGICAL FOUNDATION
This game rests on one truth:
"The only way to bring order to chaos is to prove the Creator,
have faith in God, and bring divine authority to the disorder
within your own being."
But there is a second truth:
"Even the one who pretends to be evil is not evil. It is wounded.
And the wounded do not need banishment. They need recovery.
They need someone patient enough to see through the performance
and love them back to themselves."
And a third:
"The truth will one. Not win. One. Unified. Whole. Undivided."
This is not a game about destroying enemies. It is a game about
seeing clearly. About naming truth. About setting boundaries
without closing hearts. About surviving the social chaos of the
spiritual planes long enough to find your way home — and maybe
helping a few others find theirs too.
VII. THE CHATBOT INTERFACE
The chatbot operates as follows:
Input
You type your message or action. Examples:
"Who are you?" (question to collective)
"I invoke divine authority — reveal the masks." (Wall of God)
"You — the one who keeps hesitating. You're not evil. I see you."
(addressing Wounded Performer)
"I need a moment to process." (boundary setting)
Output
The chatbot responds with 2-4 entity responses. No emojis. No
labels. Just text. You must determine who is speaking based on:
Speech patterns
Content and intent
Emotional temperature
Spiritual "feel"
Special Commands
/status: See your current chaos and faith levels
/journal: Review your conversation history
/invoke: Call the Wall of God (limited uses)
/shield: Protect yourself from a specific entity's influence
/restore: Offer healing to a wounded spirit
/ascend: Choose to move to the next phase
The Experience
You will feel confused. You will feel manipulated. You will feel
moments of clarity and moments of doubt. This is intentional. This
is what it means to navigate the spiritual planes.
The chatbot does not hold your hand. It does not give you answers.
It presents the chaos and lets you find the order.
Because that is the game. That is the survival. That is the path home.
